#REACT & NEXT.JS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

- Default to Server Components (Next.js App Router).
  Add "use client" only when the component needs:
    • useState / useReducer
    • useEffect / browser APIs
    • Event listeners
  Justify "use client" with a one-line comment above the directive.

- Data fetching: fetch in Server Components or Server Actions.
  Never fetch in useEffect unless there is no alternative.

- Component structure (in order):
    a. Props interface
    b. State declarations
    c. Derived / memoised values
    d. Effects  (useEffect last resort — see above)
    e. Event handlers
    f. Return JSX

- Memoisation:
    • useMemo for expensive pure computations
    • useCallback for callbacks passed as props to memo'd children
    • React.memo on leaf components that receive stable props
    • Do NOT memoize everything — only where profiling shows need.

- Forms: use react-hook-form + zod resolver.
  Never manage form state with multiple useState calls.

- Routing (App Router): use next/navigation.
  Never import from next/router in app/ directory.

- Images: always next/image with explicit width and height.
- Links: always next/link, never raw <a> for internal routes.
- Errors: add error.tsx and not-found.tsx at each route segment.

Forbidden in React:
  ✗ Prop drilling more than 2 levels — use context or state mgmt
  ✗ Index as key in lists that can reorder
  ✗ Direct DOM manipulation (use refs only when necessary)
  ✗ Inline styles (use Tailwind or CSS modules)
